  "notes": "Irish (Gaeilge). ~1.7M speakers (2016 census; ~80K daily L1). PERVASIVE BROAD/SLENDER DISTINCTION: every consonant has two versions (velarised 'broad' vs. palatalised 'slender'). Initial mutation: lenition (séimhiú) and eclipsis (urú). Three main dialects: Munster, Connacht, Ulster. An Caighdeán Oifigiúil = written standard. Substrate of Hiberno-English (dental stops for θ/ð). Refs: Ó Siadhail (1989), Ní Chasaide (1999).",
